{
  "global": "Patch Sphinx's included-file reading path so that `source-read` event handler modifications to `source[0]` are applied to content consumed by the `.. include::` directive, not only to top-level document reads.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Trace where `source-read` is emitted and where `.. include::` reads file bytes",
      "atomics": [
        "Locate the `source-read` emit call in `sphinx/io.py` inside `SphinxFileInput.read()` or equivalent",
        "Locate the docutils `Include` directive implementation path used by Sphinx (check `sphinx/directives/other.py` and `docutils.parsers.rst.directives.misc.Include`)",
        "Confirm that `.. include::` reads file content via `docutils` state-machine `insert_input`, bypassing `SphinxFileInput`"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Identify the exact disconnect between the emitted `source-read` result and the content used by the include directive",
      "atomics": [
        "Add debug prints to confirm `source-read` fires for the included docname but that the returned `source[0]` is not the bytes passed to `insert_input`",
        "Check whether Sphinx subclasses or wraps the docutils `Include` directive and whether it re-reads the file independently after the event fires",
        "Determine whether the included file is processed as a full Sphinx document (going through `SphinxFileInput`) or as raw RST bytes spliced inline"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Implement the fix so included file content passes through `source-read` handlers",
      "atomics": [
        "In `sphinx/io.py` (or wherever `SphinxFileInput.read` lives), extract the `source-read` emit logic into a reusable helper `_emit_source_read(app, docname, source_list)`",
        "Override or patch the `Include` directive's file-reading step to call `_emit_source_read` on the raw bytes before passing them to `insert_input`",
        "Ensure the patched path handles encoding correctly (decode to str, emit event, re-encode or pass str as docutils expects)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Write a regression test reproducing the reported scenario",
      "atomics": [
        "Create a test fixture with `index.rst` containing `.. include:: something-to-include.rst` and `&REPLACE_ME;`, plus the included file with its own `&REPLACE_ME;`",
        "Register a `source-read` handler that replaces `&REPLACE_ME;` with `REPLACED` and assert the built HTML contains no `&REPLACE_ME;` strings"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Run `sphinx-build . build` on the exact reproduction case from the bug report and confirm `grep -Rq REPLACE_ME build/*.html` exits non-zero (no match)",
    "Run the full Sphinx test suite (`tox -e py`) to confirm no regressions in include-directive or event-handling tests"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Modify `sphinx/io.py` (and/or the Sphinx `Include` directive wrapper) to call `app.emit('source-read', docname, source)` on the content of included files at the point where docutils splices them inline, so handlers that mutate `source[0]` are respected.",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Trace emission site and include read site",
        "atomics": [
          "Read `sphinx/io.py`: find `SphinxFileInput.read` and the `app.emit('source-read', self.env.docname, source)` call",
          "Read `sphinx/directives/other.py` and `docutils/parsers/rst/directives/misc.py`: find `Include.run()` and the `self.state_machine.insert_input(include_lines, source)` call",
          "Confirm via source inspection that `Insert.run()` calls `docutils.utils.relative_path` + open/read directly, never going through `SphinxFileInput`"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Pinpoint the disconnect",
        "atomics": [
          "Insert `print(docname, source[0][:80])` inside the `source-read` handler and `print` inside `Include.run` before `insert_input` to confirm the two contents diverge",
          "Verify Sphinx does not subclass `Include` in a way that already hooks the event (search `grep -r 'Include' sphinx/directives/`)",
          "Establish that the included RST is spliced as raw lines into the parent document's state machine, not processed as an independent Sphinx document read"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Implement the fix",
        "atomics": [
          "In `sphinx/io.py`, extract a module-level function `read_doc(app, env, filename)` that reads raw bytes, decodes, emits `source-read`, and returns modified source string",
          "In the Sphinx `Include` directive override (add one to `sphinx/directives/other.py` if absent), replace the raw `open().read()` with a call to `read_doc(self.env.app, self.env, path)` before calling `insert_input`",
          "Handle the encoding/newline contract: `insert_input` expects a list of lines, so split the post-event string on `\\n` after the event fires"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Write regression test",
        "atomics": [
          "Add `tests/roots/test-source-read-include/index.rst` with `.. include:: sub.rst` and a bare `&REPLACE_ME;`; add `sub.rst` with `&REPLACE_ME;`; add `conf.py` wiring the substitution extension",
          "Add `tests/test_build_html.py::test_source_read_event_on_included_files` that builds the root and asserts `'&amp;REPLACE_ME;' not in (app.outdir / 'index.html').read_text()`"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Run `sphinx-build -b html . build` in the reproduction directory and execute `grep -Rq REPLACE_ME build/index.html && echo BAD || echo OK`, expecting `OK`",
      "Run `python -m pytest tests/test_build_html.py tests/test_io.py -x -q` and confirm all tests pass with the patch applied"
    ]
  }
}
